node.text: Here’s to all the dads out there who bust their asses on the daily. The ones who show up. The ones who do the damn thing with love and respect. Hope you cashed in all that Dad credit you’re earned and enjoyed YOUR day. I know I did.  I spent today with my family and good friends and was lucky to see the setting sun in my favorite place.  Peace. #sunday #notdriving #fathersday #myturn #nobodywenttoobing #lol

node.text: I fix my boat with an angle grinder then go 130 mph while wearing a helmet and flip flops! Wanna see the full video? Click the link in my bio to see the newest episode of Finnegan’s Garage on YouTube. And there’s a bonus: you could win a new @miller_welders Multimatic 235 multiprocess MIG/TIG/Stick welder. Details on how to win are in the YouTube video. Good luck!🍀 #millerpartner #millerwelders

node.text: This wire cart began life as the hitch rack that I ran on Blasphemi at drag week a few years ago when I refused to tow a trailer behind the car. I got over the “no trailer” thing pretty quickly, as soon as I got caught in a rain with no shelter and no room to carry an EZup tent. Anyway, Newbern cut up the rack and turned it into theirs wire spool cart and today I added a bead-rolled tool tray up top. Everything you see in the cart came from the good people @wirecare_inc and I stiffened up that top tray with a 1/2 inch round Jamey Jordan Signature Series roller and machine from @mittlerbros the song is “Waiting Room” by Fugazi.

There’s also some other good displays on homes in the same neighborhood. #griswoldfamilychristmas

node.text: The grudge match between Emily Reeves and David Newbern was awesome! Em’s stick shift GTO ran mid 7s in the 1/8th and the new-to-him LS Bullet propelled to Newbern to a best pass of 6.63. The final round was run as single passes because the left Lane at paradise Dragstrip had been oiled bad. We turned the wick up on this pass and the car spun hard but there’s a lot of potential for the combo. In the end we were all winners when we witnessed Michael Wayne Cotten do the worm on a frozen dragstrip. 😂

node.text:
I blew it. last night, I had a mic in my hand and was looking straight at a crowd of Roadkill fans filling the bleachers at Roadkill Nights 2021 and got caught up in the moment of filming a new episode of Roadkill and forget to say something that I really want to to scream. I wanted to yell at the top of my lungs, “Thank You.”

The mere idea that Freiburger and I get to watch street legal drag racing on Woodward Ave each summer and that somehow, someway,  the name Roadkill is on every banner, every wall, and every shirt at this legendary event seems so far fetched that it’s nearly impossible to fathom. 

You made this happen. You and an army of folks who get it. Maybe you didn’t know it from jumpstreet. Perhaps your kids convinced you to click a link and watch a video about two dudes having fun with cars. Maybe that car show flickering on your  screen showed you that cars aren’t that complicated and that they bring families, friends and strangers together in unexplainable ways? Maybe you didn’t even consider yourself a gearhead until two dudes from SoCal with weird accents and questionable judgment made it seem OK to work on a car that nobody else saw the value in. Whatever it was, you took up with a movement that loves everybody; Import, domestic, old car, new hotness— it doesn’t matter and it doesn’t have to be perfect. It just has to roll. 

You are the reason Roadkill is about to embark on an 11th season of filming and that Dodge brought RKN back to the streets of Pontiac, Michigan, again. 

Thank you. Seriously, THANK YOU!!!! 

To quote the legendary mini trucker, Courtney Halowell, “We are part of something bigger than you or I will ever fully understand.”

RIP Tito and RIP Ernie Macias

node.text: It’s Roadkill Nights today, and this week we are all about giving back to some fans! I have not seen it yet, but today we are buying this ‘72 Duster with a 340, and we might TRADE IT FOR YOUR WORSE CAR! That’s right, we are TRADING DOWN at local cruise scenes around Detroit this week. Tomorrow afternoon we will be at Bakers in Milford looking for cars to trade. Bring something halfway decent, but worth less than the Duster, and we might trade ya. It’s going to be hectic at Bakers and we may not be able to see every car or every person, so email me pics of your potential trade that you can do TOMORROW, Sunday, at Bakers. Email HeyFreiburger@gmail.com. Stay tuned to my feed and to Finnegan999 all week as we trade and make announcements about other cruises. We buy high and trade low!

node.text: Here’s a little preview of the Dodge Hellcat Grudge Match between tv star @ericchrishon and four other car builders you  probably know from YouTube. These builders were all given 10 grand and 6 weeks to build the fastest Hellcat Red Eye to blitz the 1/8 mile Dragstrip at the street legal drags on Woodward ave during Roadkill Nights. The catch is that their car will be crushed at the end of this deal but they will get to keep the Hellcat drivetrains! Whoa gonna be there at M1 Concourse in Pontiac, Michigan tomorrow night to see it all unfold? #dodge #hellcat #fastestcarsinthedirtysouth #alextaylor #tavarish #throtl #westenchamplin #ericmalone #roadkill

node.text: Repost from @davidfreiburger using @RepostRegramApp - We need your help! Roadkill Nights is this Saturday, August 14 in Pontiac, Michigan. We are buying a ‘72 Duster with a 340 at the event, and then we are looking to trade DOWN each night at local cruise scenes. That’s right, we are trading our cars for your LESS valuable cars for several nights in a row! We need tips on the best cruise scenes to hit during the week between Roadkill Nights and Woodward Dream Cruise, so email me at HeyFreiburger@gmail.com. Once we have a schedule, I’ll post it so you know where to bring your junk to trade for our better junk. Let’s go!

node.text: It took some serious coercion and more than a little bit of whiskey to coax the elves back into the shop but I managed to get a stupid amount of Finnegan Speed and Marine apparel back in stock. I told the little buggers this was all your fault—you cleaned me out the last time we had a merch drop. I also promised them all the candy canes and cocktails they could handle plus a week away at American ninja warrior camp if they could just keep it between the lines for a little bit longer and crank out a few more shirts, hats and stickers for you guys. They gave me the middle finger and finished the job anyway. It’s amazing what a little bit of Wild Turkey will do to adjust the attitude of vertically challenged alcoholic Tailors. Hurry up before they go on the wagon again! Click the link in my Instagram bio or visit FSMGARAGE.com soon.
